examples.en: She had a long career break occasioned by her husband's job being moved to Paris.
Your behaviour has occasioned us a great deal of anxiety.
The laborious dot-and-go-one walk occasioned by his lameness.
I saw an advertisement which occasioned me much thought. (Kemble)
The happiness brought by a new baby was a timely counterpoise to the grief occasioned by a death in the family.
